        name='submit_final_result',
        args='{"final_result":"## Segment-Level FCF Proxy Analysis — Q1 2026 (SpaceX S-1)\\n\\n### Source Data (Three Months Ended March 31, 2026)\\nFrom the SpaceX S-1 MD&A segment tables (figures in $ millions):\\n\\n| Segment | Segment Adjusted EBITDA | Capital Expenditures |\\n|---|---:|---:|\\n| Space | $(351) | $1,052 |\\n| Connectivity | $2,087 | $1,332 |\\n| AI | $(609) | $7,723 |\\n\\nNote: Per the filing context, the consolidated financial statements have been retrospectively recast under common-control accounting to include xAI (merged February 2, 2026) and X Holdings (merged into xAI March 28, 2025) for all historical periods presented. The AI segment therefore reflects the recast consolidated entity, not standalone SpaceX operations.\\n\\n### Step 1 — Q1 2026 FCF Proxy (Segment Adjusted EBITDA − Capex)\\n\\n| Segment | Calculation | Q1 2026 FCF Proxy ($M) |\\n|---|---|---:|\\n| Space | $(351) − $1,052 | $(1,403) |\\n| Connectivity | $2,087 − $1,332 | $755 |\\n| AI | $(609) − $7,723 | $(8,332) |\\n\\n### Step 2 — Annualize at Q1 2026 Run-Rate (×4)\\n\\n| Metric | Calculation | Annualized ($M) |\\n|---|---|---:|\\n| Space FCF Proxy | $(1,403) × 4 | $(5,612) |\\n| Connectivity FCF Proxy | $755 × 4 | $3,020 |\\n| AI FCF Proxy | $(8,332) × 4 | $(33,328) |\\n| AI Capex (annualized) | $7,723 × 4 | $30,892 |\\n\\n### Step 3 — Years of Connectivity Annualized FCF Proxy to Fund One Year of AI Capex\\n\\nRatio = AI Annualized Capex ÷ Connectivity Annualized FCF Proxy\\n= $30,892M ÷ $3,020M\\n= **≈ 10.23 years**\\n\\n(Equivalently, using quarterly figures: $7,723M ÷ $755M = 10.23 — the 4× factor cancels.)\\n\\n### Interpretation\\nAt the Q1 2026 run-rate, it would take approximately **10.23 years** of Connectivity\'s annualized FCF proxy to fund a single year of AI segment capital expenditures. This reflects the extreme capital intensity of the AI segment (xAI), where Q1 2026 capex of $7.7B dwarfs the positive cash generation of the Connectivity (Starlink) segment. Both Space and AI segments generate negative FCF proxies at the Q1 2026 run-rate, with Connectivity being the only segment producing a positive FCF proxy.\\n\\n### Caveats\\n- \\"FCF proxy\\" here is defined per the question as Segment Adjusted EBITDA minus capex. Segment Adjusted EBITDA is a non-GAAP measure that adds back D&A, share-based compensation, and restructuring charges to segment income from operations; it does not capture working capital changes, interest, taxes, or other corporate items. This is therefore a simplified proxy, not a true free cash flow figure.\\n- Annualization assumes Q1 2026 results are representative of the full year; actual full-year results may differ materially due to seasonality, ramp curves, and one-time items.\\n\\n{\\n  \\"sources\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\"url\\": \\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\\",\\n      \\"name\\": \\"SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026) — MD&A Segment Adjusted EBITDA reconciliation and Capital Expenditures by Segment tables for the three months ended March 31, 2026\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}"}',
        parsed_args={
            'final_result': '## Segment-Level FCF Proxy Analysis — Q1 2026 (SpaceX S-1)\n\n### Source Data (Three Months Ended March 31, 2026)\nFrom the SpaceX S-1 MD&A segment tables (figures in $ millions):\n\n| Segment | Segment Adjusted EBITDA | Capital Expenditures |\n|---|---:|---:|\n| Space | $(351) | $1,052 |\n| Connectivity | $2,087 | $1,332 |\n| AI | $(609) | $7,723 |\n\nNote: Per the filing context, the consolidated financial statements have been retrospectively recast under common-control accounting to include xAI (merged February 2, 2026) and X Holdings (merged into xAI March 28, 2025) for all historical periods presented. The AI segment therefore reflects the recast consolidated entity, not standalone SpaceX operations.\n\n### Step 1 — Q1 2026 FCF Proxy (Segment Adjusted EBITDA − Capex)\n\n| Segment | Calculation | Q1 2026 FCF Proxy ($M) |\n|---|---|---:|\n| Space | $(351) − $1,052 | $(1,403) |\n| Connectivity | $2,087 − $1,332 | $755 |\n| AI | $(609) − $7,723 | $(8,332) |\n\n### Step 2 — Annualize at Q1 2026 Run-Rate (×4)\n\n| Metric | Calculation | Annualized ($M) |\n|---|---|---:|\n| Space FCF Proxy | $(1,403) × 4 | $(5,612) |\n| Connectivity FCF Proxy | $755 × 4 | $3,020 |\n| AI FCF Proxy | $(8,332) × 4 | $(33,328) |\n| AI Capex (annualized) | $7,723 × 4 | $30,892 |\n\n### Step 3 — Years of Connectivity Annualized FCF Proxy to Fund One Year of AI Capex\n\nRatio = AI Annualized Capex ÷ Connectivity Annualized FCF Proxy\n= $30,892M ÷ $3,020M\n= **≈ 10.23 years**\n\n(Equivalently, using quarterly figures: $7,723M ÷ $755M = 10.23 — the 4× factor cancels.)\n\n### Interpretation\nAt the Q1 2026 run-rate, it would take approximately **10.23 years** of Connectivity\'s annualized FCF proxy to fund a single year of AI segment capital expenditures. This reflects the extreme capital intensity of the AI segment (xAI), where Q1 2026 capex of $7.7B dwarfs the positive cash generation of the Connectivity (Starlink) segment. Both Space and AI segments generate negative FCF proxies at the Q1 2026 run-rate, with Connectivity being the only segment producing a positive FCF proxy.\n\n### Caveats\n- "FCF proxy" here is defined per the question as Segment Adjusted EBITDA minus capex. Segment Adjusted EBITDA is a non-GAAP measure that adds back D&A, share-based compensation, and restructuring charges to segment income from operations; it does not capture working capital changes, interest, taxes, or other corporate items. This is therefore a simplified proxy, not a true free cash flow figure.\n- Annualization assumes Q1 2026 results are representative of the full year; actual full-year results may differ materially due to seasonality, ramp curves, and one-time items.\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026) — MD&A Segment Adjusted EBITDA reconciliation and Capital Expenditures by Segment tables for the three months ended March 31, 2026"\n    }\n  ]\n}'
